  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there is no record of Sania Mirza participating in an Olympic bronze medal match or any recent Olympic tennis events. Sania Mirza, one of India's most accomplished tennis players, has primarily excelled in doubles, achieving significant success on the WTA Tour and in Grand Slam tournaments.\n\nHere are a few key points regarding her career and recent activities:\n\n1. **Retirement from Professional Tennis**: Sania Mirza announced her retirement from professional tennis in November 2022. Since then, she has not been active in competitive tennis tournaments, including the Olympics.\n\n2. **Olympic Participation**: Throughout her career, Sania Mirza represented India in multiple Olympic Games (2012 London and 2016 Rio de Janeiro). However, she did not medal in these events. There has been no official participation or performance by her in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics (held in 2021 due to the COVID-19 pandemic) or any events thereafter.\n\n3. **Current Endeavors**: Post-retirement, Sania Mirza has been involved in various activities, including sports commentary, mentorship for young athletes, and advocacy for sports and women's empowerment in India. There is no public information suggesting any involvement in competitive matches or controversies related to Olympic events.\n\n4. **Clarifying \"Gone Rogue\"**: The phrase \"gone rogue\" implies unexpected or uncharacteristic behavior, often in a negative context. There is no verified information or credible reports indicating that Sania Mirza has acted out of alignment with her professional demeanor or ethical standards, especially concerning Olympic matches.\n\nIf you encountered this information from a specific source, it might be a misunderstanding, misinformation, or a mix-up with another individual. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's recommended to consult official sports news outlets or Sania Mirza's verified social media profiles.",
